Description:
CENTRAL COWES – WALK TO EVERYTHING – PRIVATE GARDEN SETTING
A great opportunity to secure this well maintained brick home on 800sqm block in Cowes central where you can walk to everything including the north facing beach of Cowes. This property has successfully operated as a very lucrative holiday rental over the last 10 years with great reviews. Take advantage of growing tourist numbers to Phillip Island and live the lifestyle you have always dreamed of. This property is located in a quiet yet high exposure position in central Cowes close to both the beach, supermarkets, shops & restaurants and only a short drive to the world renowned Penguin Parade & Phillip Island Grand Prix Circuit.
Offering three large bedrooms with built in robes all with Nobo electric heating and tv points. The bathroom has walk in shower & deep relaxation bath and the large and comfortable lounge has reverse cycle heating/cooling and a gas wood heater for year around comfort. A separate dining area, plus kitchen including another reverse cycle unit and dishwasher and stone benches. The home itself was completely renovated a few years ago including polishing the original floorboards and leaving features such as the stained wood fireplace mantel and its stone surrounds, and glass French doors leading from entry foyer to lounge area.
This unique property also boast a separate fully contained unit with polished concrete floors, ensuite, tv point and a split system. A great place for family and friends, perfect for a little extra income to use as a games room or revert back to original lock up garage.
Outdoor features include an outdoor six person heated spa, sandstone paved entertaining area, established garden complete with fruit trees and high fencing for privacy. A long side driveway can accommodate up to 4 cars or boat/trailer
This wonderful property offers endless possibilities; perfect for the savvy investor, ongoing holiday rental, for your family holiday home or permanently living. Inspection by appointment only.

Description:
BRAND NEW 4 BR QUALITY BUILT HOME OPPOSITE THE PARK
Here is a unique opportunity to purchase a quality-built home by one of our premium builders within the Whytesands estate opposite the park that offers sporting facilities and amenities great for the whole family.
This premium built home meets all the needs with 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and a second large living area which can also be used as a rumpus, media room or home office and is within walking distance to the beach via the walking track. Surrounded by quality premium builds
Located close proximity to the local schools, parks, golf course, shops, eateries and race track, this is one of the most sought after positions in Cowes.
The spacious open plan kitchen, living & dining with built in pantry opens up to a large north facing rear outdoor entertainment area with double sliding doors.
Offering premium inclusions throughout this home it is the complete turn key package and more and includes:
- Bespoke landscaping
- Timber floor boards
- Double garage
- Fully fenced secure property
- LED down lights
- Stone bench tops
- Double shower in ensuite
- Large 3rd bedroom that has private access to 2nd bathroom
- Split systems for heating and cooling
- 900mm Stainless steel oven and upgraded gas cooker
- Stainless steel look dishwasher
- 6 Star Energy Rating
- Quality blinds
- Solar hot water system
- Upgraded timber facade
Coloured concrete and more.....
Call today to book in your private inspection or find out when our next open for inspection will be. A home in this location at this price won't last long.

Description:
Perfect Tranquil Retreat!
This immaculately presented single level home situated in a quiet court on a great sized allotment of approx 609 square metres is an easy walk to the Cowes shops, cafes and restaurants as well as the beautiful Cowes beach. The fabulous free flowing floor plan comprises two very comfortable living areas and three bedrooms including the master bedroom with ensuite. The well appointed and spacious open plan kitchen, living and dining area is located at the rear of the home with sliding doors opening out to a large covered north facing alfresco area, all overlooking a private, sun drenched yard and lush garden. This perfect tranquil family retreat has room for everyone to relax and enjoy this stunning home. The second living area including an electric fire place and the lovely master bedroom, featuring plantation shutters, are located to the front of the home with polished timber floors flowing through from here to the main living space. There are two additional good sized bedrooms, both with built in robes, located off the main living space serviced by a family bathroom including bath and separate shower, as well as the laundry which is just off the kitchen. An exposed aggregate concrete driveway to the large carport provides ample car parking space and there is provision to open the fence for access to the rear yard.
This exceptional home is ideal for either permanent living or as a holiday retreat.
Additional features include split system heating and cooling, quality fixtures and fittings throughout
Please call Yvette on 0414 506 795 to arrange your inspection.
This property for sale in Cowes is proudly presented to you by Ray White Real Estate Phillip Island

Description:
FAMILY FUTURE
A new home built approximately two years ago has been designed with the family in mind to relax and enjoy our Island lifestyle. Now on the market for a new family to enjoy, this impressive home has all the bells and whistles.
Beautifully laid timber flooring greets you at the entrance and throughout. Also at the entrance a door to the garage under cover is conveniently placed.
Three spacious bedrooms (master with ensuite), all with built in robes and another bathroom located close by.
A modern kitchen, larger than most, with long full Caesar stone bench tops, soft closing drawers and walk in pantry adds to the appeal of this property.
Double blinds on the double glazed windows, some with white timber shutters give it a beachy feel.
Comfortable control of the heating & cooling is controlled by the ducted reverse cycle system to all rooms, including the bathroom.
Solar Power and numerous skylights finish off the 6 star rating, achieved with these thoughtful features.
Open plan kitchen/living creates a spacious feel and a dedicated study nook divides the living/dining area.
Extra Features Include:
• Full Security System
• Full sprinkler system in landscaped gardens
• Side gate allowing access down the side for boats/caravan
• Under cover alfresco
• Outdoor shower
• Double Lock up remote garage
Call Jenni Kent for an inspection 0428 566 643

Description:
CONTEMPORARY COASTAL CHARM
Immaculate and spacious, this brand new home is the ideal investment opportunity or family beach home. Conveniently spread over a single level, this stylish home features four large bedrooms, the master bedroom includes a large walk in robe and en-suite.
The kitchen is well appointed with stainless steel appliances, generous bench space and plenty of storage. The home offers a large lounge area with warm timber flooring throughout, an open plan dining space with large double sliding doors opening out onto the north facing entertaining deck - the ideal space to relax with a morning coffee or enjoy a summer evening with friends.
The property has been beautifully landscaped with low maintenance plants and features a remote double garage which enables access to the secure back yard with a large lockable garden shed hidden away to the rear of the house.
Located in a quiet court, this property is within walking distance to local parks and children's’ playground and only a short distance from beautiful beaches, natural attractions, cafes and restaurants. This immaculate home embraces the essence of a tranquil coastal lifestyle. Arrange your private inspection today.

Description:
EASY BREAZY LIVING AT ITS BEST
Seamlessly spread over an ideal one level, moments from the Cowes foreshore beach this light filled quality home is sure to impress.
This low maintenance home features 4 spacious bedrooms, the master with ensuite including double vanity and large shower and WIR. The 4th bedroom is a great size and opens to the deck/alfresco area so could also be used as a second living area. All bedrooms have ceiling fans for comfort on those balmy summer nights.
The open plan kitchen, dining, living is immaculate complete with stainless steel appliances, light timber floors and sliding doors opening to the north facing alfresco area. An amazing space for entertaining or just sitting back enjoying the calm easy feel of the home and your coastal retreat.
Low maintenance gardens and a double garage complete the package, with additional double side access perfect for storage of the boat or caravan. This property is directly across the road from the lovely playground and walking tracks, a short stroll to the Cowes foreshore beach this home is the ideal position for the whole family.
An ideal low maintenance property for those who want to enjoy the Phillip Island coastal lifestyle, book an inspection today!

Description:
OUTSTANDING TOWNHOUSE WITH BAY VIEWS
When it’s all about the location, this fantastic property with Bay views will exceed your expectations.
The townhouse is designed over two levels, and offers on the lower level, 2 spacious bedrooms surrounding a central bathroom and large master bedroom with luxurious en-suite. The master and rear bedrooms both open onto the private north facing courtyard. The upper level provides a lovely bright kitchen with wall oven, electric cooktop and breakfast bar, which extends into a large sunny open plan living and dining area, highlighted by a wall of windows. Adjoining the lounge room, through large sliding doors, is a magnificent north facing deck with water views over the Cowes foreshore. The townhouse is offered with two carparks and the private courtyard is beautifully landscaped.
If you having been looking for the ideal investment property, this townhouse can come fully furnished and already has a strong proven rental history. Located opposite Cowes Yacht Club and the foreshore beach, this property will not last long. Arrange your private inspection today!

Description:
TheTranquil Woodland Retreat.
Nestled behind a copse of gumtrees, only a few minutes from Cowes township, this bright and spacious 3-bedroom home on a private 4000sqm (approx.) block is ready and waiting for you to make it your very own.
Surrounded by trees, a fernery and an orchard, this lovely home invites you to relax within its tranquil setting with large light-filled spaces throughout. Double glass doors lead out to a spacious outdoor entertainment area adjacent to the fernery, adorned with succulents and a beautiful water feature. A cathedral ceiling spans the length of the open-plan living and dining area, and the modern kitchen with gas cooking and plenty of bench and cupboard space. The three generously sized bedrooms each feature built-in robes, with an ensuite adjoining the master. Additional features include a fire place, split system air-conditioning, a spacious bathroom with bath, large laundry, double lock-up garage, shed with a studio and two large rainwater tanks that water the flower beds, hot house and vegetable patch. Just a few steps from the front door is a gazebo with power and water, which overlooks a spectacular pond, a perfect setting for outdoor entertainment through all the seasons; your own personal oasis.
This home is a short distance from the central shopping precinct of Cowes where you will find the convenience of supermarkets, specialty shops and numerous restaurants and cafes. Access to Cowes beach is just at the end of the road. The beautiful Summerlands Peninusula, Penguin Parade and Cat Bay, part of the National Surfing Reserve, is only a 5-minute drive. The home is also close to the local primary school and Newhaven College. Such a beautiful and private property will not stay on the market for long. We invite you to book your inspection today.
Offering
• Three spacious bedrooms with built-ins and lush carpets.
• Bright and inviting open-plan living and dining room with fireplace.
• Spacious kitchen with ample storage and gas cooking.
• Reverse cycle air conditioning.
• Gazebo overlooking a tranquil pond.
• Private block of approx. 4000 sqm.
• Charming courtyard with fernery and water feature.
• Shed with adjoining studio/study.
• Vegetable garden, orchard and hot house.
• Close to fantastic restaurants, shops and cafés.
• Walking distance to the beach and convenient to schools.
• Minutes from local buses and tourist attractions.
Must register prior to open for inspection to meet agent
